The paper discusses a new type of wireless jamming attack that involves controlling reflected signals to diminish the Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise Ratio (SINR) at the legitimate receiver. This involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
